# 🩺 IoT-Based Health Care Monitoring System with Live Streaming

This IoT project continuously monitors a patient's vital signs and streams them to a cloud platform along with a live video feed. Ideal for remote health diagnostics and emergency alerting.

## 🔍 Overview
Combines IoT sensors, microcontrollers, and cloud integration to enable real-time patient monitoring and alert generation.

## 💡 Features
- Tracks heart rate, body temperature, and oxygen levels
- Sends real-time data to a cloud dashboard
- Integrates live video streaming for remote monitoring

## 🧰 Tools & Technologies
- **Python**
- **Arduino/Raspberry Pi**
- Sensors (Heart Rate, Temperature, SpO2)
- Cloud: Firebase / ThingSpeak
- MJPEG video streaming

## 📘 What I Learned
- IoT sensor integration and Python data handling
- Streaming protocols for real-time video
- Healthcare security and data privacy

> Inspired by real-world health IoT solutions for elderly care and remote patient monitoring.
